<h2 id="rest">Rest</h2>
<p class="lead">Start by reviewing what stuck out to you from the message.</p>

<p><em>‚ÄúLike money, social media is a great servant but a terrible master.‚Äù</em> Carey Nieuwhof</p>

<p><a href="https://www.bible.com/bible/111/1co.6.12.niv">1 Corinthians 6:12</a></p>

<p><strong>58</strong>% don‚Äôt go one waking hour without checking their phone.</p>

<p><strong>59</strong>% check email as it comes in and <strong>89</strong>% check it daily on vacation.</p>

<p><strong>80</strong>% of teenagers sleep with their phones.</p>

<p><strong>84</strong>% believe they couldn‚Äôt go one day without their phones.</p>

<ul>
  <li>God has a special rest in Christ.</li>
</ul>

<p><a href="https://www.bible.com/bible/111/Heb.4.9-11.niv">Hebrews 4:9-11</a></p>

<p><em>‚ÄúYou have made us for yourself, O Lord, and our soul is restless until it finds rest in you.‚Äù</em> St. Augustine</p>

<p><a href="https://www.bible.com/bible/111/Mat.11.28-29.niv">Matthew 11:28-29</a></p>

<ul>
<li>How do we find rest?</li>
</ul>

